    "A loop diagram details the physical routing path of cable trays, conduits, and cable glands from the field instrument to the control room junction box. It shows conduit sizes, bending radii, cable tray fill percentages, cable entry sealing methods, and junction box accessibility. It also includes the installation class (hazardous area zone, temperature class), ingress protection rating, and fireproofing requirements. Loop diagrams are used for mechanical installation planning but are not relevant for electrical commissioning or signal testing.",
