    "A pressure gauge (manometer) is a device that measures and displays fluid or gas pressure, typically using a mechanical sensing element that deforms under pressure. Main types include Bourdon tube gauges (C-shaped, helical, or spiral tube), diaphragm gauges, bellows gauges, and piezometer tubes for liquids. Electronic pressure transmitters use sensors (strain gauge, capacitive, piezoelectric) to convert pressure into a standard electrical signal (4–20 mA).",
