    "IEC 61131-3 defines five languages: C/C++ — compiled native code for high-performance real-time applications; Python — interpreted script language for data processing and machine learning at the PLC edge; Java — object-oriented language for HMI integration and web service connectivity; Assembly — low-level machine code for interrupt service routines; and SQL — relational database query language for historical data retrieval from the PLC memory. Most modern PLCs support all five through optional software add-on modules.",
    "IEC 61131-3 defines three languages: BASIC — text language historically used in early programmable controllers for sequential batch control; FORTRAN — numerical computing language still used in scientific PLC applications for process optimization; and COBOL — business data processing language used in ERP-integrated PLCs for production reporting and inventory management. Most modern PLCs support all three plus vendor-specific graphical configuration tools that are not covered by the IEC standard.",
