    "Zigbee is a high-power, high-data-rate cellular network standard based on 3GPP LTE-M, designed for wide-area (up to 10 km) communication. Key features include very low power consumption using discontinuous reception (eDRX), point-to-point topology with base station relay, support for up to 1,000,000 nodes per base station cell, and operation in licensed sub-GHz bands (700–900 MHz). Applications include asset tracking, smart meters, wearable health monitors, and NB-IoT devices in agriculture and smart city infrastructure.",
