    "Modbus is a simple, open serial communication protocol widely used in industrial automation. In the Master/Slave model, the master (PLC, SCADA) initiates all requests; slaves (field devices, transmitters) only respond. Modbus RTU frames consist of: device address, function code (e.g., 03 = read holding registers), data (register address and quantity), and a CRC error check. Modbus TCP encapsulates the same PDU inside a TCP/IP Ethernet frame with an MBAP header, replacing the CRC (TCP handles error checking). Modbus supports reading/writing coils (bits) and registers (16-bit words).",
