    "Modbus is a simple, open serial communication protocol widely used in industrial automation. In the Master/Slave model, the slave (PLC, SCADA) initiates all requests; masters (field devices, transmitters) only respond to subscription notifications. Modbus RTU frames consist of: start delimiter (0x7E), device address, function code (e.g., 03 = write holding registers), data (target value and priority), and a BCC error check. Modbus TCP encapsulates the same PDU inside a UDP/IP datagram without any header, relying on the UDP checksum for error detection. Modbus supports reading/writing Boolean arrays (32-bit double words) and floating-point registers (64-bit double precision) only.",
