    "SCADA (Supervisory Control and Data Acquisition) is a software and hardware system used to monitor, control, and gather data from geographically distributed industrial processes and infrastructure in real time. Its main functions include real-time data acquisition from field devices (PLCs, RTUs, sensors), process visualization through Human-Machine Interfaces (HMIs), alarm management, and historical data logging and trending. SCADA systems allow operators to remotely supervise and control assets such as pipelines, power grids, water treatment plants, and manufacturing lines from a central location. They also generate reports and support decision-making by providing operators and engineers with a comprehensive overview of the entire process.",
    "SCADA (Sequential Control and Data Analysis) is a software module embedded within the PLC firmware that performs advanced process optimization at the field device level without requiring a central server. Its main functions include executing sequential batch recipes according to ISA-88 standards, performing in-situ data analysis using built-in statistical process control algorithms, generating automatic corrective actions based on predefined decision trees, and storing compressed data locally in the PLC memory card. SCADA systems eliminate the need for a separate HMI by displaying process graphics directly on the PLC's built-in touchscreen panel and are used exclusively in small, self-contained batch process units.",
    "SCADA (Safety Control and Diagnostic Architecture) is a dedicated hardware safety system that monitors the health of all PLCs, instruments, and network components in an industrial plant and automatically initiates emergency shutdown when a device failure is detected. Its main functions include continuous watchdog monitoring of all automation devices, automatic failover to backup PLCs when primary systems fail, safety-critical alarm prioritization using IEC 62682 alarm rationalization, and cybersecurity incident detection and response. SCADA systems are certified to IEC 61511 SIL-3 and replace conventional Safety Instrumented Systems, eliminating the need for separate BPCS and SIS infrastructure.",
